			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, I didnt want to go to this, but the situation calls for it.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;I would guess by looking at her post that in real life she is at least sixteen years old.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
You would guess wrong. But, then again, judging your posts, I would guess you are a lonely 17 year old High School student who has to come here to make yourself feel important.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;If the same group I used to drop Lucan went in and tried to kill Vox what do you think will happen? That is correct we would all die without so much as denting one of Vox's scales.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Thats why you dont use the same group you used for Lucan that you use for Vox. To quote the California Surfer phrase, &quot;Well, duh&quot;.  Thats why you post raid time and info.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;If you are level 60 you still have much work to do with your character. It's time to work on your honor. Foul language is a sure sign of a young or uneducated person.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Well it looks like the master of Role Playing has spoken. I will get to your ideas of Role Playing in a moment. Now, in regards to your statment on foul langauge, please explain that it is the sign of a young or uneducated person. I use such langauge and I am 21 year old Human Resources Manager who is currently going through the University of Arizona trying for my Degree in Political Science.  Therefore, your statement is incorrect and a sure sign of an megalomaniac<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Certainly Tanamar you can't deny that the raid organizer made greedy comments. If you think she did not I feel sorry for you.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Everything, including opinions ,are in the eye of the beholder. Therefore, just because you believe in something, doesnt mean that it is right for everybody or even true. It may be for you, but not for others.  Now, if you can not understand this, I feel sorry for you.<BR>
<BR>
Now, lets get into your comments on Role Playing a Paladin.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Also all paladins help others out&quot;<BR>
<BR>
True, they are known for that. They are also known for having no need for money. All the money a Paladin aquires is used to repair his/her armor and weapons, resupply his/her traveling needs, and the rest would be given to the church of his/her God/Goddess or given to the poor. Now, how much money do you have in the bank? I would imagine quite a lot. <BR>
<BR>
&quot;Greed has taken her over&quot;<BR>
<BR>
And I think you have been affected as well. Do you have money in your bank? Why is that? A paladin has no need for money. He/She is a warrior of their choosen God/Goddess. They believe that everything they need, their God/Goddess will provide them. If it isnt provided by their God/Goddess, then the Paladin doesn't need it. So, why do you need money in EQ again? You are the one who comes down on others for not Role Playing right?<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Death before dishonor Summoneaa. Know it and live it!&quot;<BR>
<BR>
 Well then before you dishonor yourself, give away all your money to a deserving soul or to the temple of your God/Goddess.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
 Pretty much Robin, dont try to condemn other for not Role Playing a Paladin, if you cant even do it. Thank you, I'll be here all night, Make sure to tip your waitress.<BR>
<BR>
Karreck Angelblade<BR>
Warrior of the 20th Blade<BR>
Betroxx<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
