				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Thanks Tanamar for dropping in. No offense ment to you at all. When I commented on the greedy original poster I did it because I would guess by looking at her post that in real life she is at least sixteen years old. Again I mean no offense but I'm guessing you are anywhere from twelve to fourteen years old. <BR>
<BR>
Let's look at the facts Tanamar. Before you get all mad and bent out of shape reason with me. When I was level 44 I killed Lucan with a group of six levels 44 to 56. These were my friends that I travel with much of the time. We have helped each other get the items we need to complete quests and to get items we wanted to have.<BR>
<BR>
How can you compare Lucan to Vox. If the same group I used to drop Lucan went in and tried to kill Vox what do you think will happen? That is correct we would all die without so much as denting one of Vox's scales.<BR>
<BR>
Have you ever seen me write a greedy statement? Agian you are correct you have not. I'm guessing by your description of killing Lucan you have never done it. Which in turn leads me to believe you are either not a paladin or not level 60. If you are level 60 you still have much work to do with your character. It's time to work on your honor. Foul language is a sure sign of a young or uneducated person.<BR>
<BR>
Next let's look at your statement of saying, I look even more naive by trying to use role playing. Write or wrong on thing I do in real life and while palying EQ is to be fair and to live with honor. Good question to ask yourself is would you rather live ten years and to die with nothing to your name but your honor and faith? Or live to be 200 years old and have every material thing you have ever wanted but have no honor and faith. Ultimatly that is for you to decide but I have made my decision.<BR>
<BR>
Next all you have to do Tanamar is look at the facts. Many people will be going on any Vox raid. More then likely seven or eight of those will be paladins. What makes anyone of them more desereving then the other? The fact that someone organized an open raid to kill a dragon that is usually killed the day it pops. In my mind and in many others it is wrong. Just seems silly to me that someone who plays a paladin would not understand this. Certainly Tanamar you can't deny that the raid organizer made greedy comments. If you think she did not I feel sorry for you.<BR>
<BR>
Finally if she really wanted the book there is a better way it could have been approached. Instead of saying she deserves it because she is level 50 or she is the raid organizer or that &quot;a paly has to do what a paly has to do&quot; she could have said &quot;I have been really hoping to get the page. If the page drops I would like all members of the raiding party to consider letting me loot the page. I understand that this is a large and somewhat selfish request but I would really like to go after my epic&quot;. Has a sweet ring to it.
